sec.p:
The project will proceed with the following activities:



(i) establish end-user needs and create an efficient environment for cooperative work;


(ii) design and implement the technical integration of their systems;


(iii) conduct extensive validation studies. 


neuGRID must function in a manner transparent to the end-user at the front-end interface, producing results identical to systems owned by centre of excellence but without their computational speed or storage capacity potential limitations.
The work plan is split in three workpackages which break up the project work flow into logical phases of: 



needs assessment, technical evaluation, planning, and implementation;


performance evaluation;


validation. 


Activities are split into user & system requirements analysis, algorithms and pipeline gridification, and prototype integration and validation.
